Individual Actors are created in Society Protocol
through an initialization birth event during which
they receive some energy from their parents
Upon initialization, Actors receive an account.
This account stores their identity for their life in Society Protocol.
Each account comes with account abstraction, allowing us
to initiate each actor with a chosen name and avatar.
When an actor reaches zero energy
in reserve that is considered a death event
in Society Protocol, the actors account is frozen
forever, and their programmable will goes into effect.
